HEADWORD: Carpophore
<hw>Car"po*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>karpo`s</grk> fruit + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A slender prolongation of the receptacle as an
axis between the carpels, as in Geranium and many umbelliferous
plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

